				Bayer CropScience is looking to outsource the development of a process to produce large scale batches of Axmi115v02 protein. This protein is produced in GM plants developed by Bayer CropScience for regulatory studies. 10 to 25 g of the protein are required for this purpose.
				%br/ 
				Axmi115v02 is 70% homologous to Vip3Af protein (vegetative insecticidal protein), produced by Bacillus thuringiensis. Vip3A proteins show a wide spectrum of activities against lepidopteran insects. It was reported to be 260 more active than cry proteins. 
				%br/
				The aim of this project is to develop a manufacturing process with a satisfying yield and purity above 95% and leading to the production of an active form of the protein.			
